= <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span> Independence

Ernst Röhm, despite his longstanding friendship with Hitler and the latter's pleas for him to stick to the plan, has had enough of the failing strategy and officially severed ties between the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span> and the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span>. Röhm, one of the few who dared to refer to Hitler by his first name—or even his nickname—was unique in never falling victim to Hitler's charisma or spell. His decision to break publicly with the Führer marks him as the first major figure to do so. (With Strasser's still on "sick leave", at least for now.)

Röhm is now expected to form a new political movement based on his interpretation of <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Nazi</span> ideology, calling for a "revolution" in which the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span> would serve as the spearhead to sweep away the old capitalist order and radically reshape Germany. Meanwhile, the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**Stahlhelm**</span> has severed all ties with the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span>, leaving it completely isolated politically.

Röhm himself acknowledges that a final confrontation with the government in the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span>'s current state would be suicidal, and he is focused on stemming the organization's bleeding before anything else.

