The <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span> barely manages to scrape together enough funds to rally <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span> loyalists into a new rival organization, adopting the same name. However, this force is largely insignificant, as many rank-and-file <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Storm Troopers</span> are too demoralized to continue the fight.

With Strasser and Röhm, his two closest allies, defecting from his vision, Hitler is deeply shaken. [? if nsdap_leader == "Hitler": The defection of his old friends has left him reeling, causing him to unexpectedly cancel planned speeches and party meetings. Once unwavering in his belief that destiny would ultimately grant him the chancellorship, that core conviction is now starting to falter. ?][? if nsdap_leader != "Hitler": However, with Hitler in Austria, there is little he can do to prevent the complete collapse of his movement's organization. ?]